REFERENCE   1  (residues 1 to 162)
  AUTHORS   Geib,S.M., Calla,B., Hall,B., Hou,S. and Manoukis,N.C.
  TITLE     Characterizing the developmental transcriptome of the oriental
            fruit fly, Bactrocera dorsalis (Diptera: Tephritidae) through
            comparative genomic analysis with Drosophila melanogaster utilizing
            modENCODE datasets
  JOURNAL   BMC Genomics 15, 942 (2014)
   PUBMED   25348373
  REMARK    Publication Status: Online-Only
REFERENCE   2  (residues 1 to 162)
  AUTHORS   Geib,S.M. and Hall,B.
  TITLE     Direct Submission
  JOURNAL   Submitted (07-JUN-2013) USDA-ARS, 64 Nowelo Street, Hilo, HI 96720,
            USA
COMMENT     Reads were pooled into a single fastq file for each read pair.
            This pooled sample represents transcripts from throughout the
            entire life history of B. dorsalis.  These pooled sequences were
            normalized in silico to 30x using kmer counting with scripts
            provided with Trinity v2012-10-05 (normalize_by_kmer_coverage.pl).
            These normalized reads were assembled with Trinity v2012-10-05.
            The resulting assembly was filtered to remove sequences
            representing low abundance or poorly supported transcripts and to
            remove sequences that did not contain likely open reading frames
            (non-coding).  Non-normalized reads were mapped to the Trinity
